<br>
People also fail to see the value of progressing through the game as it was released/is intended.  Sure, Kael or PoG armor is better than Fear/Hate gear, but PoG is also much harder when raid force is wearing SMRs and Tree Weaves instead of Carimine Robes and Indicolite BPs.<br>
<br>
There are also lots of less obvious reasons to progress naturally.  Some people in my own guild would totally skip Trakanon and Veeshan's Peak with all the better stuff in Velious and Luclin, but that would cause us to miss out on a lot of the 55+ spells that you accumulate from numerous Kunark dragon kills (which many of our members still need).<br>
<br>
Not to mention that the simple raid experience is very valuable. <p>Lady Sinari Dax<br>
The Platinum Queen<br>
High Council of Companions<br>
Veeshan</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinaridax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinari Dax</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/4/02 9:26:47 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwign.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wign</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/4/02 9:34:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: First Hate raid Need help </span><hr size=1> This is all great advice. I will keep all these things in mind especially the &quot;Slow zone in&quot;. I am a fast zoner usually and will make sure that I am I am not the only Wizzy there and definitely not the first to port up. I hope to get to 47 today before I go just to be safe. Thanks again and keep it coming the raid isn't scheduled until 5pm EST so I have plenty of time to keep checking back. <br>
